# Trace event instrumentation

`requestContext` exposes optional **`traceEmitter`** (injected from `chat.agent.ts` for tool runs). Stream timing so the chat UI TRACE panel stays accurate.

## Tool files (`tools/*.tools.ts`)

Wrap **every** `graphs.X.invoke()` with `graph_start` / `graph_end` (same `name` string as the graph).

```typescript
const traceEmitter = requestContext.getStore()?.traceEmitter;
const graphStart = Date.now();
traceEmitter?.({ type: "graph_start", name: "opportunity" });
const result = await graphs.opportunity.invoke(input, config);
traceEmitter?.({ type: "graph_end", name: "opportunity", durationMs: Date.now() - graphStart });
```

## Graph files (`graphs/*.graph.ts`)

Wrap **every** `agent.run()` (or equivalent agent call) inside nodes with `agent_start` / `agent_end`. Use **kebab-case** names: `"intent-inferrer"`, `"profile-generator"`, `"opportunity-evaluator"`.

```typescript
const traceEmitter = requestContext.getStore()?.traceEmitter;
const agentStart = Date.now();
traceEmitter?.({ type: "agent_start", name: "opportunity-evaluator" });
const result = await agent.run(input);
traceEmitter?.({
  type: "agent_end",
  name: "opportunity-evaluator",
  durationMs: Date.now() - agentStart,
  summary: "Evaluated 3 candidates",
});
```

New tools/graphs: follow the same pattern end-to-end.
